element.name: pub-date
element.note: http://mwebdev2.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/archivedtd/ncbi/pmc/journalmatter/>>||This element is only required at the <journal-meta> level, but can also be included in <document-meta> and <issue-meta>; the date may vary for each instance.

element.name: issue-meta
element.note: Container element for the variable information that changes with each issue, such as the date of publication, the volume and issue numbers, etc.

element.name: person-list
element.note: A container element used for lists of person(s), such as authors, editors, translators, etc., contained within document content. For groups of persons in a citation or reference list use <person-group>. ^^The following are suggested as @types for <person-list>: **editor **author **reviewer **editorial-board

element.name: sec
element.note: A headed group of material; the basic structural unit. ^^Note for @sec-type: When "general-info" is the @admin-type, the following is a suggested list of types: **copyright **subscription-info **journal-contact **associations **journal-philosophy ^^Although designed to accept any text as its value, for best practice, this attribute should be used only if the section is one of the types listed.

element.name: standing-admin
element.note: ROOT ELEMENT||There are two root elements for administrative materials: <standing-admin> and <issue-admin>. Standing-admin should be used for non-issue based and administrative materials (e.g., editorial board, information for authors, and subscription information) that are not published in an issue, but are static, such as information published on a website. ^^All documents must be assigned types. If the document is not one of the listed types or the type of document cannot be determined, the "other" attribute value may be used. @standing-admin-types include: **Editorial Board ("edboard"): can include executive editors, associate editors, etc. as well as general editorial board members. **General Journal Information ("general-info"): can include but is not limited to jounal mission statement, scope, journal contact information, subscription information, copyright and other journal-specific content. **Publisher Information ("publisher"): can include publisher philosophy, other journals published, contact information, etc. **Information for Authors ("info-for-authors"): can include article submission and formatting instructions. **Other ("other")

element.name: person-group
element.note: A container elemened used for groups of persons contained within citation elements. For lists of persons in the document content, such as editorial board members, use <person-list>.

element.name: document-title
element.note: Examples include: Editorial Board, Information For Authors, Cover, etc.

element.name: person
element.note: Container element for specific information about a person, such as name, affiliation, degree, etc.

element.name: issue-admin
element.note: ROOT ELEMENT||There are two root elements for administrative materials: <standing-admin> and <issue-admin>. ^^Issue-admin should be used for administrative materials (e.g., editorial board, information for authors, and subscription information) that are published in an issue. ^^All documents must be assigned types. If the document is not one of the listed types or the type of document cannot be determined, the "other" attribute value may be used. @issue-admin-types include: **Cover ("cover"): can include cover image, caption, and cover image copyright information. **Editorial Board ("edboard"): can include executive editors, associate editors, etc. as well as general editorial board members. **General Journal Information ("general-info"): can include but is not limited to jounal mission statement, scope, journal contact information, subscription information, copyright and other journal-specific content. **Publisher Information ("publisher"): can include publisher philosophy, other journals published, contact information, etc. **Information for Authors ("info-for-authors"): can include article submission and formatting instructions. **Other ("other")

element.name: document-meta
element.note: Container element for metadata specific to the document, as opposed to issue or standing information. Examples include the document's title, page range, copyright and contributors, etc.
